## Propagating Trace Context Through RabbitMQ Headers

The key is to **inject** the current trace context into message headers on publish and **extract** it on consume, then start a new activity linked to the extracted context.

### Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;
using RabbitMQ.Client;

private static readonly ActivitySource ActivitySource = new("ServiceA.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void PublishOrder(OrderEvent order, IModel channel)
{
    using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity("OrderEvent send", ActivityKind.Producer);

    var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
    props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

    // Inject current context into message headers
    Propagator.Inject(
        new PropagationContext(activity.Context, Baggage.Current),
        props.Headers,
        (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

    var body = JsonSerializer.SerializeToUtf8Bytes(order);
    channel.BasicPublish(exchange: "orders", routingKey: "", basicProperties: props, body: body);
}
```

### Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
private static readonly ActivitySource ActivitySource = new("ServiceB.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    // Extract context from incoming headers
    var parentContext = Propagator.Extract(
        default,
        ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
        (headers, key) =>
        {
            if (headers != null && headers.TryGetValue(key, out var value))
            {
                return new[] { Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])value) };
            }
            return Enumerable.Empty<string>();
        });

    Baggage.Current = parentContext.Baggage;

    // Start a new activity linked to the extracted parent
    using var activity = ActivitySource.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent receive",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext.ActivityContext);

    // Process the message — any downstream spans are now part of the same trace
    var order = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<OrderEvent>(ea.Body.Span);
    ProcessOrder(order);
}
```

### Why this works

1. **W3C TraceContext** (`traceparent`/`tracestate`) is injected as RabbitMQ header bytes by the propagator.
2. On consume, `Extract` rebuilds the `ActivityContext` with the original trace ID.
3. Starting a new activity with that parent context stitches both services into one distributed trace.

### Don't forget to register the ActivitySource

In both services' OTel setup:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")  // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

> **Tip:** If you switch to [MassTransit](https://masstransit.io/) or the newer `RabbitMQ.Client` 7.x `IChannel`, context propagation is built-in. The manual approach above works for any raw RabbitMQ usage.
